<div id="minimise" style="display: none; text-align: center; background-color: peachpuff; margin-top: 10px;">
<div style="font-size: 40px;">
Everyone knows it well that as of now, there has not been found a promising cure of this disease, but there still are certain ways we can contribute to the society and help minimise the spread of Covid-19.
<br>
<br>
Staying indoors is the premier of them all. If you are not in a business that the government recognises as mandatory during this crisis, abstain from stepping out of your house if it is not urgent, and even if it is, take all the precautionary measures as directed by experts to protect yourself and the society from this virus.
<br>
<br>
<li>
	Keep your face and mouth properly covered all the time when in public.
</li>
<li>
	Do not hoard essential supplies. Remember, Coronavirus spread is a two way process-the person you are interacting with too needs to have taken proper measures. A simple surgical mask will do, do not hoard N-95 masks. 
</li>
<li>
	Maintain social distancing at any cost.
</li>
<li>
	<a href="https://www.who.int/health-topics/coronavirus#tab=tab_2">Again!</a>
</li>

	
</div>
</div>

